text: Tina Røe Skaar (born 31 August 1993) is a Norwegian taekwondo practitioner. She qualified for competing at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, by winning the +67kg class in the 2016 European Taekwondo Olympic Qualification Tournament, after winning her matches against Nafia Kuş, Olga Ivanova and Reshmie Oogink. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian female taekwondo practitioners Category:European Games competitors for Norway Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 European Games
